all. Can be grown in containers with pruning. Seeds dispersed by birds. Known locally as Sampangi in South India.", "availability": "Widely cultivated - Local tropical monsoon climates nurseries, Plantshub India, Indian garden centers, temple gardens. Seeds and plants readily available."}, {"name": "Magnolia × alba (White Champaka, Pak-Lan) 🧬 🏆", "slug": "magnolia-alba-white-champaka-pak-lan", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 1, "origin": "Cultivated origin (M. champaca × M. montana hybrid), Southeast Asia and China, introduced to Taiwan 17th century. Cultivated for centuries", "traits": "Medium-sized evergreen tree to 30m, smooth silvery-grey bark, elliptical leaves 10-35cm × 4-11cm", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Heavy flowering over extended season", "growing_notes": "CULTURALLY SIGNIFICANT IN tropical monsoon climates. White version of champaca. Flowers woven into garlands for traditional ceremonies, weddings, religious offerings in Indonesia and Thailand. Essential oil extracted for perfume industry (200+ patents). Known as ''Bai Yu Lan'' (white-jade flower) in China. Thrives perfectly in Tropical monsoon tropical monsoon climate. Sterile hybrid propagated vegetatively. Popular street tree.", "availability": "Widely available - tropical monsoon climates nurseries, Indian garden centers, flower markets during season"}, {"name": "Golden Magnolia (Simhachalam Sampenga) 🌱", "slug": "golden-magnolia-simhachalam-sampenga", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 2, "origin": "India, associated with Simhachalam temple near Vishakhapatnam", "traits": "Small to medium evergreen tree", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "4-6 flowers produced daily during season", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Green Magnolia (Aaku Sampenga/Manoranjitam) 🌱", "slug": "green-magnolia-aaku-sampenga-manoranjitam", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort